record_data.record_title: Hatchet Ridge Wind, LLC - Market Based Tariff
record_data.record_plain_text:
Hatchet Ridge Wind, LLC Market-Based Rate Tariff
1. Availability: Hatchet Ridge Wind, LLC ("Hatchet Ridge") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom Hatchet Ridge has contracted.
2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by Hatchet Ridge not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of Hatchet Ridge.
3. Rates: All sales pursuant to this Rate Schedule shall be made at rates negotiated between the purchaser and Hatchet Ridge.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions for purchases of electric energy and capacity shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Hatchet Ridge.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Hatchet Ridge shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Hatchet Ridge's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Hatchet Ridge to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Hatchet Ridge's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Hatchet Ridge's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Rate Schedule.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Hatchet Ridge has requested and been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market-based rate authority, pursuant to Commission order approving this Rate Schedule: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 of the Commission's regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licenses is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. ? 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. See Letter Order, Hatchet Ridge Wind, LLC, Docket No. ER10-1362-000 (2010).
7. Seller Category: Hatchet Ridge is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a) in the following regions: Northeast, Southeast, Central, Southwest Power Pool and Northwest. Seller is a Category 2 Seller in the Southwest region.
